WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.840
Gulliver's Travels by Jonathan Swift. Young Adult Ailey Readers 2012

00:10.960 --> 00:12.100
Chapter 1 

00:12.200 --> 00:17.120
I arrive in Lilliput. Myself and my family. 

00:17.200 --> 00:23.320
I decide to travel. Disaster at sea. Lilliput.

00:23.720 --> 00:29.280
My name is Lemuel Gulliver, and this is my story. 

00:30.080 --> 00:34.980
My father came from the north of England, and I was his middle son. 

00:35.180 --> 00:39.180
I had two older brothers and two younger brothers. 

00:39.320 --> 00:44.080
We didn't have much money, but my father sent me to Cambridge University. 

00:44.180 --> 00:49.100
I was 14 years old. I was very lucky. 

00:49.500 --> 00:54.800
I studied hard, but after three years, it was time for me to start work.

00:54.900 --> 00:58.000
I went to London to work for a famous doctor. 

00:58.300 --> 01:01.500
In my free time, I studied more. 

01:01.600 --> 01:05.500
I studied navigation, mathematics, and medicine. 

01:05.800 --> 01:11.100
Why? Because I wanted to be a doctor, and I wanted to travel. 

01:11.200 --> 01:16.900
I finished my studies, and I found a job as a doctor on a ship called the swallow. 

01:18.000 --> 01:21.650
I traveled for three and a half years with the swallow.

01:21.720 --> 01:28.720
After these three and a half years, I was tired, so I decided to stay in London. 

01:28.920 --> 01:33.020
I found a small house, and I found some patience. 

01:33.120 --> 01:39.020
I found a wife. Her name was Mary, and she had 400 pounds. 

01:39.520 --> 01:42.520
But life was difficult on dry land. 

01:42.620 --> 01:47.120
I was a good doctor, but I was too honest. 

01:47.220 --> 01:53.520
The rich doctors in London were not very honest. They made a lot of money from their patients.

01:53.920 --> 02:02.720
They sold a lot of medicines to them. I didn't want to be like them. I had no choice. I had to go back to sea.

02:02.720 --> 02:09.720
For the next six years, I traveled to the East and West Indies. I made a lot of money.

02:09.720 --> 02:20.720
On the ship, I spent my free time reading. On dry land, I watched new people and learned new languages.

02:21.720 --> 02:29.720
I had enough money to stay at home with my wife and family. I stayed in London with them, and I was happy.

02:29.720 --> 02:38.720
But three years later, I had money problems again. I looked for another ship and found the antelope.

02:38.720 --> 02:45.720
Captain William Pritchard gave me a job. I was a ship's doctor again.

02:45.720 --> 02:56.720
The antelope left from Bristol on May 14, 1699. Our destination was the south seas.

02:56.720 --> 03:04.720
The journey was comfortable until we met a terrible storm. The ship was in danger from the strong wind.

03:04.720 --> 03:11.720
We went up and down and left and right. Twelve men died in the storm.

03:11.720 --> 03:20.720
Suddenly, the ship hit rocks near Van Demon's land. Disaster. The ship broke in two.

03:20.720 --> 03:27.720
Six of us jumped into a small boat. We tried to move away from the ship, but it was hard.

03:27.720 --> 03:36.720
We were not far from land when the wind hit our small boat. Suddenly, I was in the water.

03:36.720 --> 03:46.720
I never saw my five friends again. I swam and swam for hours and hours until I was so tired that I couldn't swim.

03:46.720 --> 03:56.720
Then I relaxed. I will die here, I thought. But what was this?

03:56.720 --> 04:05.720
Suddenly, I could feel land under my feet. I felt stronger now. Now I could walk.

04:05.720 --> 04:10.720
I had to walk for a long way before I arrived at the shore.

04:10.720 --> 04:18.720
It wasn't very windy now and I could see the sun. It was about eight o'clock in the evening.

04:18.720 --> 04:27.720
I walked along the beach looking for houses or some people. I was tired and it was very hot.

04:27.720 --> 04:34.720
It was November. November the 5th, I think. But that was summer in the south seas.

04:34.720 --> 04:45.720
I decided to sit down. Then I lay down. The sand was warm and soft. I went to sleep.

04:45.720 --> 04:51.720
I slept for hours. I think about nine hours.

04:51.720 --> 04:57.720
When I woke up, it was light. I decided to get up and look for help.

04:57.720 --> 05:07.720
I couldn't move my legs. I tried to move my arms, but I couldn't. I tried to move my head, but I couldn't.

05:07.720 --> 05:17.720
The reason soon became clear. Ropes. Thousands of little ropes were over my legs and my arms.

05:17.720 --> 05:26.720
The ropes were everywhere, even in my hair. The sun was very hot and its light hurt my eyes.

05:26.720 --> 05:34.720
Then something moved on my leg. It moved across my body until I could see it.

05:34.720 --> 05:40.720
It was a little man, about six inches tall.

05:40.720 --> 05:45.720
Now I could feel another forty little men walking all over me.

05:45.720 --> 05:53.720
I shouted. They ran away. They were afraid, but so was I.

05:53.720 --> 05:59.720
They soon came back. One of them came up to my face again and shouted,

05:59.720 --> 06:02.720
HIKI NŌ DIKŌ!

06:02.720 --> 06:08.720
His friends repeated the words. I didn't understand their language.

06:08.720 --> 06:17.720
I tried to move. I broke the little ropes on my left arm and tried to catch one of the little men.

06:17.720 --> 06:25.720
They ran away again, and then I heard a shout, TOLL GOOFONAC!

06:25.720 --> 06:33.720
Suddenly I felt a terrible pain in my left hand. They're throwing arrows, I thought.

06:34.720 --> 06:43.720
Some arrows went into my hand, some into my body. I tried to free my hair. More terrible pain.

06:43.720 --> 06:52.720
Then the arrows stopped, so I tried to free my right arm. The arrows started again.

06:52.720 --> 07:01.720
I must stay still, I thought. I can wait until night. These people are too small to keep me here.

07:01.720 --> 07:06.720
I was right. The arrows stopped again.

07:06.720 --> 07:12.720
Now I could hear a lot of noise. There were more little men.

07:12.720 --> 07:18.720
What are they doing, I thought? They're building something.

07:18.720 --> 07:24.720
Again, I was right. Now I could see a platform made of wood.

07:24.720 --> 07:32.720
The platform was near my head on the right. After an hour, they stopped building.

07:32.720 --> 07:37.720
Some of the little men cut the hair on my left, so I could move my head.

07:37.720 --> 07:44.720
I turned my head to the right. I could see four of the little men on the platform.

07:44.720 --> 07:48.720
They want to talk to me, I thought.

07:48.720 --> 07:57.720
One of the men was older and taller than the others. He started to speak, but I couldn't understand.

07:57.720 --> 08:05.720
Now I was quite hungry. I put my fingers on my mouth. The man understood.

08:05.720 --> 08:12.720
A few minutes later, I felt hundreds of the little men on my body. They had food for me.

08:12.720 --> 08:21.720
They put some in my mouth. I ate and ate. Then they brought something delicious to drink.

08:21.720 --> 08:29.720
I drank and drank. The little men were so happy that they danced on my body.

08:30.720 --> 08:35.720
Heketa degull! They shouted.

08:35.720 --> 08:41.720
Then a very important man arrived. He had a letter from the Emperor.

08:41.720 --> 08:50.720
I understood from his hands that the Emperor wanted to see me. I had to go to the capital city.

08:50.720 --> 08:57.720
I also understood that I wasn't free. Suddenly I felt tired.

08:57.720 --> 09:07.720
Why? Sleeping medicine in the wine, they told me later. I slept for about eight hours.

09:07.720 --> 09:21.720
When I woke up, I was in a strange cart on the way to the capital. It took 500 engineers, 900 strong men and 1500 horses to take me there.

09:21.720 --> 09:27.720
They were very clever people. We arrived at the capital two days later.

09:27.720 --> 09:30.720
The Emperor was there to meet me.

09:30.720 --> 09:44.720
This is your new home, he said. He pointed to an old church. Some of the men put new ropes on my legs, but now I could walk a little.

09:45.720 --> 09:54.720
The next morning, the Emperor came to see me again with his family. With him were carts of food and drink.

09:54.720 --> 10:03.720
The Emperor was taller than all his countrymen and his face was strong. He was about 28 years old.

10:03.720 --> 10:12.720
He spoke to me, but I couldn't understand. I tried English, Dutch, Latin, French, Spanish and Italian.

10:12.720 --> 10:19.720
No one could understand me, and after about two hours, they went away.

10:19.720 --> 10:28.720
I sat outside the church, watching some soldiers. Suddenly I felt an arrow near my eye.

10:28.720 --> 10:36.720
A group of six little men fired more arrows at me. The soldiers were angry with the little men.

10:36.720 --> 10:44.720
I picked up the six men and put five of them in my pocket. I put the other man near my mouth.

10:44.720 --> 10:51.720
Now the soldiers were worried. I put the little man down and he ran away.

10:51.720 --> 10:57.720
I don't eat little men, I said, smiling.

10:57.720 --> 11:04.720
One by one, I pulled the other little men out of my pocket and they all ran away.

11:04.720 --> 11:11.720
The soldiers were all very happy indeed. The little people began to trust me.

11:11.720 --> 11:22.720
After about two weeks, 600 beds arrived at my new house. The little men put them all together to make one big bed.

11:22.720 --> 11:27.720
After that, I was very comfortable.

11:27.720 --> 11:37.720
Everybody in Lilliput now knew about me. Rich people, lazy people and curious people all came to see me.

11:37.720 --> 11:47.720
The emperor often came to see me too. He also talked to all the important people in the land. Some people were worried.

11:47.720 --> 11:54.720
My food was very expensive and I was dangerous. They wanted to kill me. The emperor said no.

11:54.720 --> 11:58.720
He remembered the six little men who fired arrows.

11:58.720 --> 12:06.720
Find me the best teachers, he said. This man must learn our language.

12:06.720 --> 12:11.720
After about three weeks, I could speak the language quite well.

12:11.720 --> 12:16.720
The emperor sometimes came to give me conversation practice.

12:16.720 --> 12:20.720
Every time he came, I asked him for my freedom.

12:20.720 --> 12:25.720
Be patient, he always said.

12:25.720 --> 12:31.720
I was now very comfortable with my bed, the language and some new clothes.

12:31.720 --> 12:36.720
When the men brought me my new clothes, they made a list of all my things.

12:36.720 --> 12:44.720
Later that day, the emperor came to visit. He had thousands of soldiers with him.

12:44.720 --> 12:48.720
I want to take your sword, he said.

12:48.720 --> 12:54.720
I pulled out my sword slowly. The sunlight caught the sword.

12:54.720 --> 12:59.720
The light hurt the soldier's eyes and they were all afraid.

12:59.720 --> 13:05.720
I put the sword on the ground and hundreds of soldiers took it away.

13:05.720 --> 13:13.720
After that, I gave my other things to the emperor, my money, my comb and my notebook.

13:13.720 --> 13:16.720
The soldiers took them all away.

13:16.720 --> 13:23.720
I was lucky. When they made the list of my things, they didn't find my secret pocket.

13:23.720 --> 13:28.720
In that pocket were my glasses and a pocket telescope.

13:28.720 --> 13:37.720
I didn't tell the emperor about them. I wanted to keep them for myself.

13:37.720 --> 13:41.720
Chapter Two, My Life in Lilliput

13:41.720 --> 13:53.720
Lilliput, Freedom, War with Blafuscu, Escape to Blafuscu, I returned to England.

13:53.720 --> 13:57.720
People in Lilliput seemed more friendly now.

13:57.720 --> 14:02.720
Boys and girls played in my hair and they called me Man Mountain.

14:02.720 --> 14:05.720
The horses weren't scared of me now.

14:05.720 --> 14:10.720
People enjoyed coming to see me. I became a tourist attraction.

14:10.720 --> 14:16.720
One day, the emperor asked me to stand up with my feet apart.

14:16.720 --> 14:20.720
Then he told his soldiers to march under me.

14:20.720 --> 14:24.720
Everyone enjoyed the parade.

14:24.720 --> 14:28.720
Now I will give you your freedom, the emperor said.

14:28.720 --> 14:33.720
But there are some rules. In fact, there are nine rules.

14:33.720 --> 14:38.720
If you agree, you will be free.

14:38.720 --> 14:41.720
The emperor gave me a piece of paper.

14:41.720 --> 14:48.720
Rules. One, the man mountain must not leave Lilliput without permission.

14:48.720 --> 14:53.720
Two, he must not come into the city without permission.

14:53.720 --> 14:57.720
Three, he must stay on the roads.

14:57.720 --> 15:04.720
Four, he must be careful. Our people are very small.

15:04.720 --> 15:10.720
Five, he must carry urgent messages for the emperor.

15:10.720 --> 15:16.720
Six, he must help us in our war with Blafuscu.

15:16.720 --> 15:21.720
Seven, he must help us build new houses.

15:21.720 --> 15:27.720
Eight, he must make a map of our country.

15:27.720 --> 15:38.720
Nine, he can have food and drink equal to 1,724 Lilliputians.

15:38.720 --> 15:45.720
I had no problem with the rules. I asked a friend about the calculation for food and drink.

15:45.720 --> 15:50.720
The best mathematicians in the country decided this, he said.

15:50.720 --> 15:56.720
They calculated your height. You are exactly 12 times taller than us.

15:56.720 --> 16:05.720
Your volume is therefore 12 cubed. As you know, 12 cubed equals 1,724.

16:05.720 --> 16:13.720
I checked the mathematics. 12 times 12 times 12 equals 1,724.

16:13.720 --> 16:22.720
You are very clever people, I answered, and very good at economics.

16:22.720 --> 16:30.720
About two weeks later, I had a visitor. His name was Reldresal and he was an important man.

16:30.720 --> 16:38.720
He sat in my hand and we talked. He told me about some of the problems in Lilliput.

16:38.720 --> 16:46.720
He was worried about political differences. He was also worried about war, war with Blafuscu.

16:46.720 --> 16:50.720
The biggest problem, he said, is eggs.

16:50.720 --> 16:59.720
Eggs, I asked, surprised. Yes, eggs, big Indians and little Indians.

16:59.720 --> 17:05.720
I was confused. What are big Indians and little Indians?

17:06.720 --> 17:10.720
Everyone in Lilliput has boiled eggs for breakfast.

17:10.720 --> 17:17.720
In the past, everyone cut their boiled egg at the big end. They were big Indians.

17:17.720 --> 17:26.720
Then an emperor cut his finger. He made a law. Everyone had to cut their boiled egg at the little end.

17:26.720 --> 17:32.720
We became little Indians. Some people changed, but other people didn't.

17:32.720 --> 17:37.720
There were protests. Some big Indians left Lilliput.

17:37.720 --> 17:43.720
Today, there are still problems. The emperor of Blafuscu helps the big Indians.

17:43.720 --> 17:50.720
So, we are at war with Blafuscu. About eggs.

17:50.720 --> 17:54.720
Can I help? I asked.

17:54.720 --> 17:59.720
I hope so, replied Reldrasal, sadly.

17:59.720 --> 18:08.720
The emperor of Blafuscu has a lot of ships. He has more than us, and the ships are ready to attack us.

18:08.720 --> 18:15.720
Let me speak to the emperor, I said. I had an idea.

18:15.720 --> 18:20.720
The empire of Blafuscu is very near to Lilliput.

18:20.720 --> 18:26.720
The channel between the two countries is less than a mile wide, and the water is not very deep.

18:26.720 --> 18:31.720
Before I went to see the emperor, I went to the beach.

18:31.720 --> 18:39.720
I looked at the Blafuscu ships through my pocket telescope. There were about 50 ships.

18:39.720 --> 18:47.720
I went quickly to the palace. I told the emperor my idea, and he was very happy indeed.

18:47.720 --> 18:51.720
I went home to prepare some small ropes.

18:51.720 --> 18:59.720
The next morning, I went to the shore. I took off my coat and my shoes and swam across the channel.

18:59.720 --> 19:05.720
When I got near to the emperor of Blafuscu's ships, his soldiers were scared.

19:05.720 --> 19:12.720
Some of them jumped into the water. Some of them fired arrows at me, and I was worried about my eyes.

19:13.720 --> 19:19.720
Then I remembered my glasses and put them on. My job was very easy.

19:19.720 --> 19:27.720
I put ropes on all the emperor of Blafuscu's ships. Then I pulled them across the channel to Lilliput.

19:27.720 --> 19:37.720
The emperor of Lilliput was very happy. He gave me a special reward. I was a nardak, like a lord, dear reader.

19:38.720 --> 19:43.720
The emperor was so happy that he decided to send me to Blafuscu again.

19:43.720 --> 19:47.720
You can kill all the big Indians, he said.

19:47.720 --> 19:56.720
Everyone will cut their eggs from the little end, everyone in the world. I will be emperor of the whole world.

19:56.720 --> 20:04.720
No, that's not right, I shouted. I can't help you. I don't want to kill people.

20:04.720 --> 20:09.720
I don't want to kill people because of eggs.

20:09.720 --> 20:14.720
The emperor was surprised, and then he was angry.

20:14.720 --> 20:19.720
Don't trust the emperor, my friend said later that evening.

20:19.720 --> 20:26.720
Some of the emperor's friends are angry with you. You are a nardak, and they want to be nardaks.

20:26.720 --> 20:33.720
They will say bad things about you. The emperor will change.

20:33.720 --> 20:39.720
I'll be very careful. You can't always trust emperors, I said.

20:39.720 --> 20:45.720
A few weeks later, the most important Blafuscu's came to Lilliput.

20:45.720 --> 20:55.720
We must end the war, they said to the emperor. We don't want to fight anymore. It's time for us to be friends.

20:55.720 --> 20:58.720
The emperor of Lilliput said yes.

20:58.720 --> 21:04.720
The emperor of Blafuscu had to pay a lot of money, but the war was over.

21:04.720 --> 21:08.720
There was a big dinner to celebrate the end of the war.

21:08.720 --> 21:16.720
At the dinner, I met the emperor of Blafuscu. I liked him, and I talked to him for a long time.

21:16.720 --> 21:23.720
I was lucky. He was very important to me later.

21:23.720 --> 21:29.720
Now that I was a nardak, life was different. I didn't build houses now.

21:29.720 --> 21:33.720
I had time to find out more about Lilliput.

21:33.720 --> 21:40.720
I talked to a lot of people, and I learned to write Lilliputian. This was very difficult.

21:40.720 --> 21:45.720
Lilliputian writing is not from the left to the right like the Europeans.

21:45.720 --> 21:50.720
It is not from the right to the left like Arabic writers.

21:50.720 --> 21:55.720
It is diagonal, from one corner of the paper to the other.

21:55.720 --> 22:02.720
There are many other differences. For example, Lilliputians believe that the earth is flat.

22:02.720 --> 22:06.720
They also have some very strict laws.

22:06.720 --> 22:16.720
I lived very well in Lilliput. I had 300 cooks, 20 waiters, and lots and lots of other servants.

22:16.720 --> 22:21.720
People began to talk. They said I was very expensive.

22:21.720 --> 22:25.720
Many of the emperor's friends were angry with me.

22:25.720 --> 22:35.720
They began to talk to the emperor. My friend was right. The emperor of Lilliput began to change.

22:35.720 --> 22:39.720
He didn't want to fight for us, one said.

22:39.720 --> 22:43.720
He talked to the emperor of Blevver School, said another.

22:43.720 --> 22:48.720
He wants to live in Blevver School, said a third man.

22:48.720 --> 22:58.720
Oh no, you're right, said the emperor. He will fight against us. We must kill him.

22:58.720 --> 23:02.720
Later that night, my good friend came to see me.

23:02.720 --> 23:06.720
You must leave Lilliput, he said.

23:06.720 --> 23:15.720
I know, I answered. It's too dangerous for me here. We made a plan.

23:15.720 --> 23:22.720
That night, I said goodbye to my Lilliputian friend. I swam to Blevver School.

23:22.720 --> 23:25.720
I took a ship and put my things in it.

23:25.720 --> 23:28.720
I pulled the ship across the channel with me.

23:28.720 --> 23:32.720
The people of Blevver School were very pleased to see me.

23:32.720 --> 23:36.720
They sent a message to the emperor of Blevver School.

23:36.720 --> 23:41.720
Almost immediately, the emperor and his wife arrived at the shore.

23:41.720 --> 23:45.720
The people of Blevver School were not scared of me.

23:45.720 --> 23:50.720
The emperor was very kind to me, but there was one problem.

23:50.720 --> 23:56.720
There was no house for me in Blevver School, so I slept outside.

23:56.720 --> 24:00.720
Three days after my arrival, I went for a walk.

24:00.720 --> 24:07.720
I went to the northeast of the island. I saw something in the sea.

24:07.720 --> 24:13.720
Was it a boat? I took off my coat and shoes and swam to it.

24:13.720 --> 24:19.720
It was a boat, an empty boat, and it was my size.

24:19.720 --> 24:24.720
I swam back to the shore and went immediately to the city.

24:24.720 --> 24:30.720
I asked for a meeting with the emperor. He was happy to see me.

24:30.720 --> 24:35.720
Your Majesty, I began. I need your help.

24:35.720 --> 24:39.720
I will help you if I can," he answered.

24:39.720 --> 24:46.720
Thank you, Your Majesty. I need twenty ships and three thousand men.

24:46.720 --> 24:50.720
The emperor was surprised. Why?

24:50.720 --> 24:54.720
There is a large boat in the sea in the northeast.

24:54.720 --> 25:01.720
I need your help to bring it here. I can use the boat to return to my country.

25:01.720 --> 25:07.720
The emperor was very kind. He gave me the ships and the men.

25:07.720 --> 25:11.720
We brought the boat back to Blevver School.

25:11.720 --> 25:16.720
Before I left, the emperor received a letter from Lilliput.

25:16.720 --> 25:20.720
The emperor of Lilliput was very, very angry.

25:20.720 --> 25:25.720
Send the man mountain back to Lilliput, he wrote.

25:25.720 --> 25:29.720
The emperor of Blevver School sent a letter back.

25:29.720 --> 25:35.720
I'm very sorry, he wrote, but I cannot send him back to you.

25:35.720 --> 25:40.720
The man mountain is very kind. He is a peaceful man.

25:40.720 --> 25:44.720
He stopped the war between us.

25:44.720 --> 25:50.720
The emperor showed me his letter. He asked me to stay in Blevver School.

25:50.720 --> 25:54.720
I will protect you, he said.

25:54.720 --> 25:59.720
No, I must leave, I answered.

25:59.720 --> 26:04.720
The emperor helped me. He gave me food and drink for the journey.

26:04.720 --> 26:07.720
He also gave me some money.

26:07.720 --> 26:11.720
I took some of the little animals with me to show people at home.

26:11.720 --> 26:17.720
I wanted to take some of the little men with me too, but the emperor said no.

26:17.720 --> 26:26.720
On the 24th of September, 1701 at 6 in the morning, I left Blevver School.

26:26.720 --> 26:29.720
My journey was very comfortable.

26:29.720 --> 26:32.720
The first day, the weather was good.

26:32.720 --> 26:37.720
I stopped near a small island and slept for a few hours.

26:37.720 --> 26:40.720
The next day was the same.

26:40.720 --> 26:46.720
On the third day, at about three o'clock in the afternoon, I saw a ship.

26:46.720 --> 26:50.720
To my surprise, the ship was English.

26:50.720 --> 26:53.720
I reached the ship about two hours later.

26:53.720 --> 26:57.720
The captain was a very kind man.

26:57.720 --> 27:00.720
Where are you going? I asked.

27:00.720 --> 27:05.720
England, he answered. We are returning from Japan.

27:05.720 --> 27:10.720
Everyone on the ship was curious about my story.

27:10.720 --> 27:14.720
They didn't believe that the people on Lilliput were so small.

27:14.720 --> 27:17.720
You're mad, they said.

27:17.720 --> 27:21.720
Let me show you something, I answered.

27:21.720 --> 27:24.720
I showed them my little animals.

27:24.720 --> 27:27.720
Now they believed me.

27:27.720 --> 27:32.720
The journey was very comfortable and we soon arrived home.

27:32.720 --> 27:35.720
I made a lot of money with my little animals.

27:35.720 --> 27:40.720
I took them to markets in London and I showed them to people.

27:40.720 --> 27:43.720
People paid a lot to see them.

27:43.720 --> 27:46.720
Then I sold them for a hundred pounds.

27:46.720 --> 27:50.720
Now I was rich.

27:50.720 --> 27:55.720
I stayed with my wife and family and I bought a new house.

27:55.720 --> 28:00.720
But I didn't want to stay in England. I wanted to travel.

28:00.720 --> 28:04.720
I gave my wife fifteen hundred pounds.

28:04.720 --> 28:08.720
I said goodbye to her, my son and my daughter.

28:08.720 --> 28:11.720
We were all very sad.

28:11.720 --> 28:13.720
I left England again.

28:13.720 --> 28:17.720
The name of my ship was the adventure.

28:18.720 --> 28:25.720
I will tell you all about my adventures on the adventure in the next chapter.

28:26.720 --> 28:28.720
Chapter 3

28:28.720 --> 28:31.720
My Journey to Broading Nag

28:31.720 --> 28:34.720
I go back to sea.

28:34.720 --> 28:37.720
I arrive at the land of giants.

28:37.720 --> 28:40.720
I become a tourist attraction.

28:40.720 --> 28:45.720
I live with the king and queen.

28:45.720 --> 28:51.720
On the 20th of June, 1702, I left England on the adventure.

28:51.720 --> 28:57.720
We had a very good journey south and spent the winter at the Cape of Good Hope.

28:57.720 --> 29:00.720
In the spring, we sailed again.

29:00.720 --> 29:05.720
We passed Madagascar and sailed towards the Moluca Islands.

29:05.720 --> 29:07.720
The weather was very calm.

29:07.720 --> 29:09.720
Too calm.

29:09.720 --> 29:13.720
Captain Nicholas was a very good sailor.

29:13.720 --> 29:16.720
He understood weather.

29:16.720 --> 29:22.720
There will be a terrible storm tomorrow, a monsoon, he said one day.

29:22.720 --> 29:24.720
He was right.

29:24.720 --> 29:27.720
The storm continued for days.

29:27.720 --> 29:30.720
No one knew where we were.

29:30.720 --> 29:34.720
We had lots of food, but we didn't have much water.

29:34.720 --> 29:38.720
We started to look for land.

29:38.720 --> 29:43.720
On the 16th of June, 1703, we saw land.

29:43.720 --> 29:47.720
Some of us got into a small boat and went towards the shore.

29:47.720 --> 29:51.720
When we arrived, we started to look for water.

29:51.720 --> 29:54.720
We went in different directions.

29:54.720 --> 29:59.720
I didn't see any people, and I didn't find any water.

29:59.720 --> 30:04.720
I was tired, so I started to go back to the boat.

30:04.720 --> 30:09.720
When I got back to the shore, I couldn't see the boat.

30:09.720 --> 30:14.720
Then I saw it, at sea, moving quickly.

30:14.720 --> 30:20.720
Behind it, there was a very tall man, a giant.

30:20.720 --> 30:24.720
He tried, but couldn't catch the boat.

30:24.720 --> 30:29.720
I ran in the opposite direction.

30:29.720 --> 30:32.720
I ran for miles.

30:32.720 --> 30:34.720
I arrived at a field.

30:34.720 --> 30:39.720
The field was full of wheat, but it was very, very tall.

30:39.720 --> 30:45.720
Suddenly another giant man appeared, then another, then a woman.

30:45.720 --> 30:48.720
There were seven of them.

30:48.720 --> 30:51.720
What are they doing, I thought?

30:51.720 --> 30:53.720
They're farmers.

30:53.720 --> 30:57.720
Oh no, they're cutting the wheat.

30:57.720 --> 31:01.720
I ran and ran, but the farmers came nearer.

31:01.720 --> 31:04.720
I stopped, very tired.

31:04.720 --> 31:10.720
My wife, I thought, my poor wife and my poor children.

31:10.720 --> 31:13.720
Why did I leave England?

31:13.720 --> 31:16.720
I don't want to die here.

31:16.720 --> 31:20.720
I thought about Lilliput and the little people.

31:20.720 --> 31:22.720
They were scared of me.

31:22.720 --> 31:26.720
Now I was scared of someone much bigger than me.

31:26.720 --> 31:30.720
At that very moment, I saw a foot.

31:30.720 --> 31:34.720
No! Help! Stop!

31:34.720 --> 31:37.720
I shouted loudly.

31:37.720 --> 31:40.720
The farmer stopped.

31:40.720 --> 31:43.720
He looked at the ground in front of him.

31:43.720 --> 31:46.720
Then he saw me.

31:46.720 --> 31:48.720
He looked at me for a while.

31:48.720 --> 31:50.720
I understood his thoughts.

31:50.720 --> 31:54.720
I looked like this when I see a strange animal.

31:54.720 --> 31:58.720
When it hurt me, I think.

31:58.720 --> 32:02.720
After a while, he picked me up carefully.

32:02.720 --> 32:06.720
He held me between his thumb and a finger.

32:06.720 --> 32:08.720
I was scared.

32:08.720 --> 32:11.720
I was very high in the air.

32:11.720 --> 32:13.720
Don't drop me!

32:13.720 --> 32:15.720
I shouted.

32:15.720 --> 32:18.720
Ouch! You're hurting me!

32:18.720 --> 32:21.720
He seemed to understand.

32:21.720 --> 32:25.720
The farmer put me into his pocket.

32:25.720 --> 32:28.720
He walked towards his friends.

32:28.720 --> 32:31.720
Look at this, I think, he said.

32:31.720 --> 32:35.720
I didn't understand the language, but I could guess.

32:35.720 --> 32:38.720
The farmer put me on the ground.

32:38.720 --> 32:41.720
His friends sat down in a circle.

32:41.720 --> 32:43.720
They watched me.

32:43.720 --> 32:45.720
I tried to talk to them.

32:45.720 --> 32:48.720
I tried many different languages.

32:48.720 --> 32:52.720
They couldn't really hear me, and they couldn't understand.

32:52.720 --> 32:57.720
The farmers tried to talk to me, but the noise was very loud.

32:57.720 --> 33:00.720
It hurt my ears.

33:00.720 --> 33:04.720
After a while, the farmer carried me to his house.

33:04.720 --> 33:07.720
He was very careful.

33:07.720 --> 33:09.720
He called his wife.

33:09.720 --> 33:12.720
She was scared and ran away.

33:12.720 --> 33:17.720
She came back after a minute or two and was very kind to me.

33:17.720 --> 33:22.720
It was lunchtime, and she put a very big dish onto the table.

33:22.720 --> 33:25.720
The family came to eat.

33:25.720 --> 33:28.720
They were very curious.

33:28.720 --> 33:35.720
In total, there were the farmer and his wife, their three children, and an old grandmother.

33:35.720 --> 33:39.720
The farmer's wife gave me some food and drink.

33:39.720 --> 33:44.720
Suddenly, a giant cat jumped up to sit on the wife's knees.

33:45.720 --> 33:50.720
I was scared for a moment, but I think the cat was more afraid of me.

33:50.720 --> 33:56.720
After the meal, the nurse came into the room with the farmer's enormous baby.

33:56.720 --> 33:59.720
This was a terrible moment.

33:59.720 --> 34:02.720
The baby saw me and immediately picked me up.

34:02.720 --> 34:05.720
He put me into his mouth.

34:05.720 --> 34:07.720
I was very lucky.

34:07.720 --> 34:11.720
The farmer's wife pulled my legs and I was free.

34:11.720 --> 34:16.720
Then the farmer's wife took me upstairs and put me into a bedroom.

34:16.720 --> 34:18.720
She locked the door.

34:18.720 --> 34:21.720
I slept for about two hours.

34:21.720 --> 34:26.720
When I woke up, I looked around the room.

34:26.720 --> 34:31.720
Then I saw them, two enormous rats.

34:31.720 --> 34:33.720
They wanted to eat me.

34:33.720 --> 34:37.720
I took out my sword and killed the first one.

34:37.720 --> 34:40.720
The second ran away.

34:40.720 --> 34:46.720
The farmer's wife came in at that moment and saved me.

34:46.720 --> 34:50.720
I liked the farmer's daughter very much.

34:50.720 --> 34:54.720
She was nine years old and about 40 feet tall.

34:54.720 --> 34:57.720
She made a little bed for me.

34:57.720 --> 35:01.720
She also made seven little shirts for me.

35:01.720 --> 35:04.720
She was my teacher, too.

35:04.720 --> 35:08.720
Very quickly, I began to understand their language.

35:08.720 --> 35:12.720
She called me Grildrig, little man.

35:12.720 --> 35:16.720
Everyone in the family then called me Grildrig.

35:16.720 --> 35:20.720
Soon, everyone in the country called me Grildrig.

35:20.720 --> 35:26.720
Her name was Glumdow Klitch, and she was very, very kind to me.

35:26.720 --> 35:32.720
Glumdow Klitch stayed with me all the time I was in Broading Nag.

35:32.720 --> 35:35.720
Everyone in the village knew about me.

35:35.720 --> 35:41.720
I was a strange animal, just like a human, but very small.

35:41.720 --> 35:46.720
When visitors came to the house, the farmer put me on the table.

35:46.720 --> 35:50.720
I spoke to the people in their language.

35:50.720 --> 35:53.720
One visitor made a suggestion to the farmer.

35:53.720 --> 35:56.720
Put him in a box and take him to the market.

35:56.720 --> 35:59.720
People will pay to see him, he said.

35:59.720 --> 36:02.720
Glumdow Klitch was afraid.

36:02.720 --> 36:06.720
Don't hurt him, she said.

36:06.720 --> 36:11.720
The next day, the farmer put me in a box to take me to the market.

36:11.720 --> 36:13.720
Glumdow Klitch came with us.

36:13.720 --> 36:17.720
The journey was uncomfortable in my little box.

36:17.720 --> 36:22.720
When we arrived at the village, the farmer found a room at a hotel.

36:22.720 --> 36:25.720
He brought people to see me.

36:25.720 --> 36:30.720
Glumdow Klitch asked me questions and I answered in their language.

36:30.720 --> 36:33.720
A school boy threw a peanut at me.

36:33.720 --> 36:38.720
It didn't hit me. I was very lucky.

36:38.720 --> 36:40.720
The farmer was very happy.

36:40.720 --> 36:47.720
He decided to take me to all the markets in Broading Nag.

36:47.720 --> 36:52.720
Traveling was very difficult for me and very uncomfortable.

36:52.720 --> 36:54.720
I became ill.

36:54.720 --> 36:56.720
The farmer was not worried.

36:56.720 --> 37:00.720
I must sell him before he dies, he thought.

37:00.720 --> 37:04.720
Luckily, a message came from the Queen.

37:04.720 --> 37:08.720
She wanted to see me immediately so we went to the palace.

37:08.720 --> 37:11.720
She was very kind.

37:11.720 --> 37:14.720
Where are you from? She asked.

37:14.720 --> 37:17.720
England, I replied.

37:17.720 --> 37:21.720
And why did you come to Broading Nag?

37:21.720 --> 37:24.720
I told her about my travels.

37:24.720 --> 37:27.720
The Queen was very interested.

37:27.720 --> 37:30.720
She decided to buy me.

37:30.720 --> 37:35.720
How much must I give you? She asked the farmer.

37:35.720 --> 37:39.720
A thousand gold pieces he answered.

37:39.720 --> 37:42.720
Your Majesty, I said.

37:42.720 --> 37:45.720
Yes, Grildrig?

37:45.720 --> 37:47.720
I have one question.

37:47.720 --> 37:52.720
Can Glumdow Klitch come too? She is my nurse and my teacher.

37:52.720 --> 37:58.720
Glumdow Klitch was happy, the Queen was happy, and the farmer was happy.

37:58.720 --> 38:04.720
He was rich, and his daughter lived in the royal palace.

38:04.720 --> 38:08.720
One day, the Queen took me to see the king.

38:08.720 --> 38:11.720
He was surprised.

38:11.720 --> 38:14.720
Is that your new pet? He asked.

38:14.720 --> 38:16.720
What is it?

38:16.720 --> 38:19.720
He's not an animal, she answered.

38:19.720 --> 38:21.720
Listen!

38:21.720 --> 38:26.720
The Queen asked me some questions, and I answered in her language.

38:26.720 --> 38:30.720
The king was interested in my story too.

38:30.720 --> 38:32.720
He called Glumdow Klitch.

38:32.720 --> 38:36.720
Is his story true? He asked.

38:36.720 --> 38:39.720
Yes, she answered.

38:39.720 --> 38:42.720
At first, the king was not sure.

38:42.720 --> 38:46.720
Perhaps I was a clockwork toy.

38:46.720 --> 38:50.720
So he called the three most intelligent people in broadening nag.

38:50.720 --> 38:54.720
They looked at me, and they talked to me.

38:54.720 --> 39:02.720
He isn't an animal. He isn't fast, and he can't climb trees, one said.

39:02.720 --> 39:08.720
He isn't a man, said another. He's too small.

39:08.720 --> 39:13.720
He's a freak, a freak of nature, they all said.

39:13.720 --> 39:17.720
Your Majesty! I shouted. I'm a man.

39:17.720 --> 39:20.720
I come from a country called England.

39:20.720 --> 39:24.720
In England, there are millions of men and women like me.

39:24.720 --> 39:29.720
In my country, the trees and the animals are in proportion to us.

39:29.720 --> 39:35.720
The three intelligent people laughed at me.

39:35.720 --> 39:41.720
The king was a fair man. He was still interested in my story.

39:41.720 --> 39:45.720
Look after him, he said to the queen.

39:45.720 --> 39:51.720
Give him food. Build a house for him. I like him.

39:51.720 --> 39:54.720
The queen called a carpenter.

39:54.720 --> 39:59.720
Make a beautiful house for this man, she said.

39:59.720 --> 40:06.720
The carpenter was very clever. He made a very comfortable box for me.

40:06.720 --> 40:11.720
It had windows, a bed, chairs, a table, and a wardrobe.

40:11.720 --> 40:16.720
It was perfect for travelling and for living.

40:16.720 --> 40:21.720
The queen liked me. I always had dinner with her.

40:21.720 --> 40:29.720
She found toys, silver plates, knives, and forks for me, and she cut my food for me.

40:29.720 --> 40:35.720
Every Wednesday, Wednesdays were holidays, the king and queen had lunch together.

40:35.720 --> 40:41.720
The king liked talking to me. He talked about my country and Europe.

40:41.720 --> 40:46.720
He asked about government, laws, religion, and education.

40:46.720 --> 40:52.720
Sometimes he laughed, but he always listened.

40:52.720 --> 40:57.720
Sometimes life in broadening nag was dangerous for a little man.

40:57.720 --> 41:03.720
One day, I opened my window and there were twenty giant wasps outside.

41:03.720 --> 41:11.720
Luckily, I had my sword. They attacked me, so I killed them all one by one.

41:11.720 --> 41:18.720
I kept some wasps dings as souvenirs. I had problems with giant flies too.

41:18.720 --> 41:25.720
I often travelled with the king and queen. Broading nag was a very large country.

41:25.720 --> 41:32.720
European map makers are very bad. They think there is no large country between Japan

41:32.720 --> 41:40.720
and California. When I returned to England, I will correct their maps, I thought.

41:40.720 --> 41:45.720
The mountains in the north of broadening nag are thirty miles high.

41:45.720 --> 41:50.720
People catch fish in the rivers, not in the sea. Why?

41:50.720 --> 41:57.720
Because the fish in the sea are too small. In fact, they are just like ours in England.

41:57.720 --> 42:03.720
There are fifty-one cities in broadening nag and a very large number of villages.

42:03.720 --> 42:10.720
The cities are very beautiful, and there are a lot of royal palaces and temples.

42:10.720 --> 42:17.720
The king began to trust me. He often asked questions about England.

42:17.720 --> 42:24.720
We have two islands, and we have some land in another country, America, I said.

42:24.720 --> 42:32.720
We have a king and a parliament. Parliament has two houses, the House of Lords and the House of Commons.

42:32.720 --> 42:41.720
We also have judges. We pay tax to the government. We have very good soldiers and very good sailors.

42:41.720 --> 42:51.720
Why do you need soldiers? He asked. Soldiers are very expensive. Farmers are better for the country.

42:51.720 --> 42:57.720
We are a very powerful country, I explained. We have very good guns.

42:57.720 --> 43:04.720
We can kill a lot of people in a very short time, so we stay powerful.

43:04.720 --> 43:10.720
I can help you make guns like ours. The king was very angry.

43:10.720 --> 43:16.720
No, he shouted. I love science, and I love art.

43:16.720 --> 43:21.720
My people study mathematics, philosophy, history and poetry.

43:21.720 --> 43:28.720
I think you are horrible people. You make war on other countries for power.

43:28.720 --> 43:35.720
I don't make war on other countries. I don't need big guns to kill other people.

43:35.720 --> 43:45.720
I need farmers to grow food for them. We didn't speak about England again.

43:45.720 --> 43:56.720
Chapter 4. I travel to La Puta. I leave Broading Nag. I return to England. I meet pirates.

43:56.720 --> 44:01.720
I visit the flying island of La Puta.

44:01.720 --> 44:07.720
After two years in Broading Nag, I began to think about my freedom.

44:07.720 --> 44:13.720
It seemed impossible. Everyone was so big, and I was so small.

44:13.720 --> 44:19.720
At the beginning of the third year, the king and queen decided to travel to the south coast.

44:19.720 --> 44:27.720
They wanted to visit their people there. I traveled with them in my now very comfortable box.

44:27.720 --> 44:30.720
Glumdalklitch came too.

44:30.720 --> 44:36.720
At the end of our journey to the south, Glumdalklitch and I were very tired.

44:36.720 --> 44:40.720
I had a cold, and Glumdalklitch was very ill.

44:40.720 --> 44:45.720
I wanted some fresh air, but Glumdalklitch wanted to sleep.

44:45.720 --> 44:47.720
She called a boy.

44:47.720 --> 44:51.720
Take Grildrig to the sea, she said.

44:51.720 --> 44:56.720
I don't feel very well, so I will stay here.

44:56.720 --> 45:02.720
Be very careful. Look after Grildrig well.

45:02.720 --> 45:09.720
Glumdalklitch was very sad. Perhaps she could see into the future.

45:10.720 --> 45:17.720
The boy carried me in my box down to the sea. It took about half an hour.

45:17.720 --> 45:21.720
I was very tired, and I fell asleep.

45:21.720 --> 45:26.720
I don't really know what happened next. Perhaps the boy went swimming.

45:26.720 --> 45:32.720
Perhaps he put the box down just for a minute, but suddenly I woke up.

45:32.720 --> 45:38.720
What's this? Why is the box moving so fast? I thought.

45:38.720 --> 45:46.720
I was scared. I looked out of my window. I could see sky and clouds.

45:46.720 --> 45:54.720
I was now very high in the sky. I was in the claws of a giant bird.

45:54.720 --> 46:00.720
It knows I'm in here. It will eat me, I thought, afraid.

46:00.720 --> 46:07.720
Help! I shouted out of the window. Help!

46:07.720 --> 46:20.720
Suddenly, the box began to fall. It fell down and down. With a splash, it fell into the sea.

46:20.720 --> 46:26.720
In the water, in the box, I thought about poor Glumdalklitch.

46:26.720 --> 46:35.720
I thought about the king and queen. Please don't be angry with Glumdalklitch, I said to myself.

46:35.720 --> 46:45.720
Then I thought about my situation. Will someone rescue me? Will I die in the water here?

46:45.720 --> 46:56.720
After about four scary hours, I heard a noise. It was a ship. Help! Help! I shouted.

46:56.720 --> 47:00.720
Who's there? A man answered in English.

47:00.720 --> 47:05.720
Lemuel Gulliver! I shouted, help me, please!

47:05.720 --> 47:13.720
The ship's carpenter made a hole in the box and I walked out. The sailors were very surprised.

47:13.720 --> 47:25.720
They seemed small to me. Was I back in Lilliput? No. They were the same size as me.

47:25.720 --> 47:32.720
The destination of the ship was England. On the journey, I spent a lot of time with the captain.

47:32.720 --> 47:37.720
I told him about Broddingnag. He didn't believe me.

47:37.720 --> 47:46.720
You're mad, he said. Luckily, I had the wasp sting and some other souvenirs of Broddingnag.

47:46.720 --> 47:49.720
When he saw them, he believed my story.

47:50.720 --> 47:57.720
Write a book about it, he said. Perhaps I will, I answered.

47:57.720 --> 48:03.720
I arrived home on the 3rd of June, 1703, about nine months later.

48:03.720 --> 48:11.720
My wife was very happy to see me. My wife and daughter seemed very small to me.

48:11.720 --> 48:19.720
You will never go to see again, she said. She was wrong.

48:19.720 --> 48:29.720
Ten days later, a man came to my house. His name was William Robinson, and he was the captain of the Hopewell.

48:29.720 --> 48:35.720
He was like a brother to me. He came to visit me often.

48:35.720 --> 48:43.720
One day, he said, I want to go to India. Will you come with me? I need a good ship's doctor.

48:43.720 --> 48:49.720
Yes, I said, I'll be very happy to come with you.

48:49.720 --> 48:55.720
On the 5th of August, 1706, we left England again.

48:55.720 --> 49:04.720
In April, the next year, we arrived in Madras. We stayed there for a few weeks because some sailors were ill.

49:04.720 --> 49:11.720
When we set off again, there was a terrible storm. We didn't know where we were.

49:11.720 --> 49:20.720
On the 10th day, pirates saw our ship. Some of the pirates were Dutch, and some were Japanese.

49:20.720 --> 49:27.720
I spoke Dutch quite well, so said, please take the ship, but don't kill us.

49:28.720 --> 49:31.720
The Japanese pirate was angry.

49:31.720 --> 49:37.720
Put him in a canoe, alone, he said. Let him die at sea.

49:37.720 --> 49:44.720
The pirates took our sailors onto their ship. They put me into a canoe.

49:44.720 --> 49:49.720
I was alone at sea, again.

49:49.720 --> 49:54.720
When I was a long way from the pirate ship, I took out my pocket telescope.

49:54.720 --> 49:58.720
Through it, I saw some small islands.

49:58.720 --> 50:02.720
I sailed towards the first island, but it was very rocky.

50:02.720 --> 50:07.720
I found some eggs, ate them, and slept under a rock.

50:07.720 --> 50:12.720
The next day, I sailed to another island, then another.

50:12.720 --> 50:16.720
On the 5th day, I arrived at the last island.

50:16.720 --> 50:23.720
I found some more eggs. On this island, there was a small cave.

50:23.720 --> 50:29.720
I slept a little. I was quite worried now. I was very tired.

50:29.720 --> 50:34.720
When I die here, I thought.

50:34.720 --> 50:39.720
When I left the cave, it was quite late the next morning.

50:39.720 --> 50:43.720
The sun was hot and the sky was clear.

50:43.720 --> 50:49.720
Suddenly, it went quite dark. I looked up.

50:49.720 --> 50:59.720
There was a large cloud in the sky. But, no, it wasn't a cloud. What was it?

50:59.720 --> 51:07.720
It started to come down. I took out my pocket telescope. I could see people on it.

51:07.720 --> 51:12.720
It was a very large island in the sky.

51:12.720 --> 51:17.720
I was happy to see people, so I waved and waved.

51:17.720 --> 51:20.720
Some people on the island saw me.

51:20.720 --> 51:23.720
The island came down more.

51:23.720 --> 51:28.720
More people on the island in the sky came to look. They waved at me.

51:28.720 --> 51:32.720
The island was now very near to me.

51:32.720 --> 51:36.720
Help me! Help me! I shouted.

51:36.720 --> 51:41.720
The next minute, I saw a seat on a rope.

51:41.720 --> 51:45.720
The seat came down from the island towards me.

51:45.720 --> 51:52.720
I sat on the seat and the people on the island pulled me up.

51:52.720 --> 51:57.720
On the island in the sky, I saw some very strange people.

51:57.720 --> 52:03.720
Their eyes looked in different directions. Their clothes had a lot of symbols on them.

52:03.720 --> 52:11.720
Sons, moons, stars, and musical instruments. They seemed very distracted.

52:11.720 --> 52:15.720
Their servants told them when to speak and when to listen.

52:15.720 --> 52:22.720
The people on the island were very kind. They took me to the royal palace immediately.

52:22.720 --> 52:28.720
The king was also very kind. He sat on a chair in the middle of the room.

52:28.720 --> 52:32.720
There were mathematical instruments all around him.

52:32.720 --> 52:38.720
He asked me some questions, but of course, I didn't understand his language.

52:38.720 --> 52:41.720
Then dinner arrived.

52:41.720 --> 52:48.720
The food was very strange. The lamb was triangular, the bread was conical,

52:48.720 --> 52:52.720
and the sausages looked like musical instruments.

52:52.720 --> 52:55.720
A group of musicians played the music.

52:55.720 --> 52:59.720
I didn't like the music at all. It was terrible.

52:59.720 --> 53:04.720
After dinner, the king sent me away with a man.

53:04.720 --> 53:10.720
He had pens and paper. He was my language teacher.

53:10.720 --> 53:17.720
He taught me the names of the shapes, the moon and stars, and all the musical instruments.

53:17.720 --> 53:23.720
After a few days, I began to understand the language.

53:24.720 --> 53:28.720
The name of the island in the sky is La Puta.

53:28.720 --> 53:32.720
La Puta flies over a larger island under it.

53:32.720 --> 53:35.720
The name of this island is Balnibabi.

53:35.720 --> 53:40.720
The capital city, Lagado, is on Balnibabi.

53:40.720 --> 53:47.720
The houses on La Puta are all very strange. There are no 90 degree angles in the houses.

53:47.720 --> 53:51.720
This is because the La Putans are not practical.

53:51.720 --> 53:56.720
They are interested in mathematics, music and astrology.

53:56.720 --> 54:06.720
The men of La Puta are also very scared. They are afraid that, one day, a falling star will hit their island.

54:06.720 --> 54:12.720
The women of La Puta live a comfortable life, but they are very bored.

54:12.720 --> 54:16.720
The king uses physics to control the movement of La Puta.

54:16.720 --> 54:21.720
He also uses La Puta to control the people of Balnibabi.

54:21.720 --> 54:27.720
Dear reader, the people of Balnibabi are very oppressed.

54:27.720 --> 54:32.720
The king can use La Puta to stop rain and block the sun.

54:32.720 --> 54:40.720
If the people of Balnibabi cause a lot of trouble, the people of La Puta throw rocks at them.

54:41.720 --> 54:48.720
The people on the island of La Puta were kind to me, but they weren't curious about me at all.

54:48.720 --> 54:55.720
I was quite interested in both mathematics and music, but the men were quite boring.

54:55.720 --> 54:59.720
I began to talk to women, children and servants.

54:59.720 --> 55:07.720
The La Puta men were surprised at this, but the women, children and servants talked about more interesting things than the men.

55:08.720 --> 55:13.720
I studied hard, and now I could speak their language very well.

55:13.720 --> 55:16.720
But there was nothing for me here.

55:16.720 --> 55:21.720
After two months on the island, I wanted to leave.

55:21.720 --> 55:27.720
There was one La Puta man I liked. He was a very important lord.

55:27.720 --> 55:34.720
He was very intelligent, very practical and very interested in the world around him.

55:34.720 --> 55:37.720
Everyone said he was stupid.

55:37.720 --> 55:42.720
Why? Because he didn't like La Puta music.

55:42.720 --> 55:45.720
He often came to talk to me in my room.

55:45.720 --> 55:51.720
What's Europe like? What's the legal system in England?

55:51.720 --> 55:57.720
What's Lilliput like? What's Brodynag like? He asked.

55:57.720 --> 56:01.720
One day we talked about travelling.

56:01.720 --> 56:04.720
Could you help me? I asked him.

56:04.720 --> 56:07.720
How? He answered.

56:07.720 --> 56:10.720
Will you talk to the king for me?

56:10.720 --> 56:18.720
I want to leave. I want to travel to Balnibarbi and to other places in the world.

56:18.720 --> 56:23.720
Yes, I'll talk to the king, he promised.

56:23.720 --> 56:28.720
On the 16th of February, I left La Puta.

56:28.720 --> 56:34.720
The king gave me a present. Some money to help me on Balnibarbi.

56:34.720 --> 56:46.720
The island of La Puta went down in the sky. When we were near Balnibarbi, I went down on the seat on the rope.

56:46.720 --> 56:48.720
Chapter 5

56:48.720 --> 56:52.720
I visit strange and wonderful places.

56:52.720 --> 57:03.720
On Balnibarbi, inside the academy, the magical island, I meet Hannibal.

57:03.720 --> 57:13.720
When I reached Balnibarbi, I was very happy. I walked to Legato. I'm sure you remember that this is the capital city.

57:13.720 --> 57:21.720
I had the name of a man to visit in Legato, Lord Munodi. He was a friend of my friend on La Puta.

57:21.720 --> 57:27.720
The man was very happy to meet me. I stayed in his house.

57:27.720 --> 57:34.720
The next morning, he took me to visit the capital. It was about the same size as London.

57:34.720 --> 57:42.720
The houses were very strange and very badly built. The people in the streets walked fast.

57:42.720 --> 57:47.720
They looked a little wild. Their clothes were old.

57:47.720 --> 57:58.720
Then we walked into the countryside. Again, the people were poor. I was surprised because the land was good.

57:58.720 --> 58:05.720
Lord Munodi's house was different from the others. His garden was also more beautiful than the others.

58:05.720 --> 58:10.720
I asked Lord Munodi why.

58:10.720 --> 58:20.720
About 40 years ago, the Leputin government built an academy here in Legato. The academy studies building, agriculture and languages.

58:20.720 --> 58:29.720
The professors have some very strange ideas. They tell the Leputin government their ideas and the government makes stupid laws.

58:29.720 --> 58:37.720
They are not practical. My house is different because I break the laws.

58:37.720 --> 58:40.720
Can I visit the academy? I asked.

58:40.720 --> 58:44.720
Yes. About you must go alone, he answered.

58:44.720 --> 58:51.720
I hate the academy and I will never ever go there. You must take some money with you.

58:51.720 --> 58:57.720
They never have any money for their studies, so they beg from visitors.

58:57.720 --> 59:04.720
The following day, I visited the academy. The dean was very happy to meet me.

59:04.720 --> 59:10.720
The academy was very large with about 500 rooms.

59:10.720 --> 59:17.720
In the first room, there was an old man. He told me about his studies.

59:17.720 --> 59:25.720
I'm working on a very important project. I'm trying to make sunlight from cucumbers.

59:25.720 --> 59:33.720
We take the sunlight out of the cucumbers, put it in a bottle and then we can use it on cold days.

59:33.720 --> 59:38.720
Very interesting, I said. I gave him some money.

59:38.720 --> 59:45.720
I went into another room. The smell was so bad that I left immediately.

59:45.720 --> 59:53.720
In another room, there was a very clever engineer. He had a new way of building houses.

59:53.720 --> 01:00:02.720
He built the roof first and the walls second. At the end, he built the foundations.

01:00:02.720 --> 01:00:10.720
In the next room, there was a man who couldn't see. His job was to mix colors for artists.

01:00:10.720 --> 01:00:14.720
He did this by smell and by touch.

01:00:14.720 --> 01:00:21.720
I visited a lot of rooms in the academy, but I didn't see any practical ideas.

01:00:21.720 --> 01:00:26.720
The dean wanted to show me more rooms on the other side of the academy.

01:00:26.720 --> 01:00:31.720
There I visited the school of languages. There were three professors there.

01:00:31.720 --> 01:00:36.720
Their job was to improve their language.

01:00:36.720 --> 01:00:41.720
What exactly are you doing? I asked one professor.

01:00:41.720 --> 01:00:47.720
This is my language machine, he answered. It's making our words shorter.

01:00:47.720 --> 01:00:51.720
All words will soon be very, very short.

01:00:51.720 --> 01:00:54.720
Very interesting, I said.

01:00:54.720 --> 01:01:00.720
My job is more interesting, said the second professor.

01:01:00.720 --> 01:01:07.720
There is no need for words in our language. Speaking is very bad for people.

01:01:07.720 --> 01:01:10.720
Too much speaking makes people ill.

01:01:10.720 --> 01:01:15.720
In my system, we don't need words, we need things.

01:01:15.720 --> 01:01:21.720
People will soon communicate by carrying things in their pockets.

01:01:21.720 --> 01:01:25.720
For short conversations, you only need a few things.

01:01:25.720 --> 01:01:31.720
Of course, for long conversations, you need servants to carry your things.

01:01:31.720 --> 01:01:36.720
For very long conversations, you just need a card.

01:01:36.720 --> 01:01:42.720
My system has one great advantage. It's a universal language.

01:01:42.720 --> 01:01:46.720
You can communicate with people from all over the world.

01:01:46.720 --> 01:01:51.720
But my language machine is the best, said the first professor.

01:01:51.720 --> 01:01:57.720
No, yours is too complicated, said the second.

01:01:57.720 --> 01:02:01.720
I gave them some money and left quickly.

01:02:01.720 --> 01:02:06.720
Next, I spent a very short time at the School of Mathematics.

01:02:06.720 --> 01:02:11.720
There the scientists wrote formulas on edible paper.

01:02:11.720 --> 01:02:15.720
They then ate them immediately.

01:02:15.720 --> 01:02:20.720
I now understood that all these professors were mad.

01:02:20.720 --> 01:02:26.720
Balnebabi was poor and unhappy because of these professors and their silly ideas.

01:02:26.720 --> 01:02:31.720
I decided to leave the academy and Balnebabi as soon as possible.

01:02:31.720 --> 01:02:35.720
I wanted to go back to Europe.

01:02:35.720 --> 01:02:39.720
The next day, I spoke to Lord Munodi.

01:02:39.720 --> 01:02:42.720
I want to go back to England, I said.

01:02:42.720 --> 01:02:45.720
I'm not surprised, he answered.

01:02:45.720 --> 01:02:47.720
Perhaps I can help.

01:02:47.720 --> 01:02:52.720
The King of Lugnag has a very good relationship with the Emperor of Japan.

01:02:52.720 --> 01:02:57.720
It must be possible to get from there to Japan and from Japan to England.

01:02:57.720 --> 01:03:03.720
Why don't you go to Lugnag? It's a small island and it's quite near.

01:03:03.720 --> 01:03:08.720
Thank you, I said. That's a very good idea.

01:03:08.720 --> 01:03:12.720
I said goodbye to Lord Munodi and left Lagado.

01:03:12.720 --> 01:03:16.720
I traveled to the port of Maldonada.

01:03:16.720 --> 01:03:20.720
When I arrived, I spoke to a man at the port.

01:03:20.720 --> 01:03:24.720
When's the next ship for Lugnag? I asked.

01:03:24.720 --> 01:03:27.720
In five weeks he answered.

01:03:27.720 --> 01:03:33.720
I decided to spend the time visiting a different island, Glubdubdrib.

01:03:33.720 --> 01:03:37.720
Its other name is the Magical Island.

01:03:37.720 --> 01:03:40.720
It's a very small island.

01:03:40.720 --> 01:03:44.720
The King of the Magical Island is a magician.

01:03:44.720 --> 01:03:46.720
He has a very special power.

01:03:46.720 --> 01:03:51.720
He can call ghosts from the past to be his servants.

01:03:51.720 --> 01:03:55.720
They can only work for him for 24 hours.

01:03:55.720 --> 01:04:01.720
When I arrived at the Magical Island, I went immediately to see the King.

01:04:01.720 --> 01:04:07.720
He was very happy to see me and invited me to stay at the Royal Palace.

01:04:07.720 --> 01:04:12.720
It was a little strange at first, the servants were always different.

01:04:12.720 --> 01:04:17.720
One evening, the King invited me to a special dinner.

01:04:17.720 --> 01:04:20.720
After dinner, we talked.

01:04:20.720 --> 01:04:27.720
I like you, Galiva. He said, I have an interesting idea.

01:04:27.720 --> 01:04:30.720
Do you want to meet some people from the past?

01:04:30.720 --> 01:04:33.720
Yes, please. I replied.

01:04:33.720 --> 01:04:37.720
Who? Let me think.

01:04:37.720 --> 01:04:40.720
Alexander the Great, I answered.

01:04:40.720 --> 01:04:45.720
Call him, then he will appear, said the King.

01:04:45.720 --> 01:04:49.720
Alexander the Great, I called.

01:04:49.720 --> 01:04:53.720
Two seconds later, Alexander appeared.

01:04:53.720 --> 01:04:57.720
It was difficult to understand his Greek at first.

01:04:57.720 --> 01:05:00.720
Another, said the King.

01:05:00.720 --> 01:05:03.720
Soon, Hannibal appeared.

01:05:03.720 --> 01:05:08.720
Look! He's crossing the Alps. I shouted.

01:05:08.720 --> 01:05:12.720
I then asked to see Caesar and Pompey.

01:05:12.720 --> 01:05:15.720
Then the whole Senate of Rome appeared.

01:05:15.720 --> 01:05:18.720
Caesar and Brutus came near to me.

01:05:18.720 --> 01:05:23.720
I spoke to Brutus, a very fine man.

01:05:23.720 --> 01:05:27.720
The next day, I decided to call some more ghosts.

01:05:27.720 --> 01:05:30.720
Homer and Aristotle were interesting.

01:05:30.720 --> 01:05:33.720
I called Descartes and Gascendi.

01:05:33.720 --> 01:05:36.720
Aristotle was pleased to meet them.

01:05:36.720 --> 01:05:45.720
Oh dear, I made some mistakes in my philosophy, he said, after a long conversation.

01:05:45.720 --> 01:05:49.720
The next day, I called some ghosts from modern history.

01:05:49.720 --> 01:05:52.720
They were very disappointing.

01:05:52.720 --> 01:05:56.720
I called people from the past and recent past.

01:05:56.720 --> 01:05:58.720
It was strange.

01:05:58.720 --> 01:06:03.720
All the people from the recent past were very disappointing.

01:06:03.720 --> 01:06:06.720
At the end of my stay on the magical island,

01:06:06.720 --> 01:06:13.720
I understood more about the problems of my country and the problems of Europe.

01:06:13.720 --> 01:06:16.720
It was time for me to leave.

01:06:16.720 --> 01:06:22.720
I thanked the King of the magical island very much and went back to Maldonada.

01:06:22.720 --> 01:06:25.720
There, I found a ship for Leugnag.

01:06:25.720 --> 01:06:28.720
The journey took a month.

01:06:28.720 --> 01:06:35.720
It is easy to communicate with the people of Leugnag because many of them speak the language of Balnibabi.

01:06:35.720 --> 01:06:39.720
The Leugnagians are very polite, generous people.

01:06:39.720 --> 01:06:43.720
They all seem to be very happy.

01:06:43.720 --> 01:06:48.720
Soon after I arrived, the King invited me to the royal palace.

01:06:48.720 --> 01:06:54.720
I wanted to be polite, too, so I learnt some words in Leugnagian.

01:06:54.720 --> 01:06:58.720
When I arrived at the palace, I said these words to the King.

01:06:58.720 --> 01:07:06.720
Ickbling Lothrobskuseirombeheob, mashing out Zwimodbalkgufsliob had good lobashed.

01:07:06.720 --> 01:07:08.720
He was very pleased.

01:07:08.720 --> 01:07:12.720
He invited me to stay in the royal palace.

01:07:12.720 --> 01:07:15.720
I stayed for three months.

01:07:16.720 --> 01:07:20.720
One day a Leugnagian asked me a strange question.

01:07:20.720 --> 01:07:23.720
Would you like to meet any mortal?

01:07:23.720 --> 01:07:25.720
What do you mean?

01:07:25.720 --> 01:07:30.720
Some people here are immortal. They live forever.

01:07:30.720 --> 01:07:33.720
How wonderful, I said.

01:07:33.720 --> 01:07:37.720
Yes, I would like to learn from any mortal.

01:07:37.720 --> 01:07:39.720
They will teach me a lot about life.

01:07:39.720 --> 01:07:43.720
Perhaps I can learn something special.

01:07:43.720 --> 01:07:48.720
Unfortunately, the immortals are not nice people.

01:07:48.720 --> 01:07:55.720
They are angry, horrible, jealous, miserable, and extremely talkative.

01:07:55.720 --> 01:08:00.720
Because they are different from other people, they don't have friends.

01:08:00.720 --> 01:08:03.720
They are also very ugly.

01:08:03.720 --> 01:08:07.720
They have a strange blue spot on their heads.

01:08:07.720 --> 01:08:11.720
The oldest immortal I met was 200 years old.

01:08:11.720 --> 01:08:17.720
He was very, very angry and very, very horrible.

01:08:17.720 --> 01:08:22.720
I began to understand that the Leugnagians don't like the immortals.

01:08:22.720 --> 01:08:25.720
They don't want to live forever.

01:08:25.720 --> 01:08:31.720
Perhaps that's why the Leugnagians are so happy.

01:08:31.720 --> 01:08:36.720
After three months at the royal palace, I decided to leave.

01:08:36.720 --> 01:08:40.720
It was time to go back to England and my family.

01:08:40.720 --> 01:08:42.720
The king was sorry.

01:08:42.720 --> 01:08:48.720
Stay here, he said. You can work for my government.

01:08:48.720 --> 01:08:55.720
I'm sorry, I answered. I must go home. I must see my family again.

01:08:55.720 --> 01:09:04.720
The king was very generous. He gave me some gold and a beautiful red diamond.

01:09:04.720 --> 01:09:10.720
In early May, I left Leugnag. I arrived in Japan two weeks later.

01:09:10.720 --> 01:09:15.720
In Japan, I began to look for a ship to take me to Europe.

01:09:15.720 --> 01:09:19.720
It was very difficult to find a ship.

01:09:19.720 --> 01:09:25.720
After a few weeks, I found a Dutch ship. I spoke to the captain.

01:09:25.720 --> 01:09:28.720
Where are you from? He asked.

01:09:28.720 --> 01:09:31.720
Holland, I answered.

01:09:31.720 --> 01:09:37.720
The Dutch and the English weren't good friends at this time. It was better to be Dutch.

01:09:37.720 --> 01:09:42.720
Luckily, I knew the Dutch language very well.

01:09:42.720 --> 01:09:47.720
Captain Theodoras Van Groot was happy to take me.

01:09:47.720 --> 01:09:53.720
He needed a ship's doctor. I invented some stories about my family in Galdaland.

01:09:53.720 --> 01:09:56.720
No one knew I was English.

01:09:58.720 --> 01:10:02.720
In June, we finally left Japan.

01:10:02.720 --> 01:10:06.720
The journey was long, but there were no adventures.

01:10:06.720 --> 01:10:09.720
We stopped at the Cape of Good Hope.

01:10:09.720 --> 01:10:14.720
This time, we only stayed for two days because the weather was good.

01:10:14.720 --> 01:10:19.720
We got fresh water and sailed away immediately.

01:10:19.720 --> 01:10:24.720
On the 6th of April, 1710, we arrived at Amsterdam.

01:10:24.720 --> 01:10:28.720
I immediately found another boat from Amsterdam to England.

01:10:28.720 --> 01:10:32.720
Four days later, I was home.

01:10:32.720 --> 01:10:40.720
My wife was very happy to see me. She was very well, and so were my children.

01:10:40.720 --> 01:10:45.720
I stayed at home in England for five very happy months.

01:10:45.720 --> 01:10:49.720
Then, I started to think about traveling again.

01:10:49.720 --> 01:10:53.720
I spoke to some friends.

01:10:53.720 --> 01:10:57.720
Didn't you sail on the adventure a few years ago?

01:10:57.720 --> 01:11:01.720
One of them said, yes, why?

01:11:01.720 --> 01:11:07.720
Well, they need a new captain. Why don't you speak to the owner?

01:11:07.720 --> 01:11:11.720
I traveled to Portsmouth to meet the owner of the adventure.

01:11:11.720 --> 01:11:17.720
After many years as a ship's doctor, I understood navigation very well.

01:11:17.720 --> 01:11:21.720
It was time for me to become the captain of a ship.

01:11:21.720 --> 01:11:25.720
The owner was happy. He remembered me from before.

01:11:25.720 --> 01:11:29.720
The job is yours, he said.

01:11:29.720 --> 01:11:35.720
I was very pleased. Now, I needed a ship's doctor.

01:11:35.720 --> 01:11:39.720
I found a young man. He was very good at his job.

01:11:39.720 --> 01:11:43.720
Then, I said goodbye to my wife and children.

01:11:43.720 --> 01:11:48.720
We left Portsmouth on the 7th of September, 1710.

01:11:48.720 --> 01:11:54.720
Our destination? The South Seas. Again.

